cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.DS, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new loss function for multi-label learning. It also discusses a learning algorithm and a statistical learning bound for the loss. 

It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as the proposed loss function can improve predictions in many problems. 

The paper also uses a real-data tag prediction problem, which suggests it could belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision). 

The regularization approximation mentioned in the paper could also place it in the category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). 

Finally, the use of the Wasserstein distance as a metric could suggest it belongs to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
